<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <%= render "shared/head" %>
  </head>

  <body>
    <%# Phase 7.5 (requirement.md §5.14 v12) — @event is only ever a real, persisted record here
        via EventScoped or Admin::EventsController's own #show/#edit/etc. (never #index/#new,
        where there's no specific event yet to be "inside") — #persisted? is what actually gates
        this, not bare presence, so a brand-new unsaved @event (Admin::EventsController#new/
        a failed #create re-render) correctly still shows the account-level sidebar. %>
    <%= render layout: "shared/console_shell", locals: {
      home_path: user_root_path,
      nav_items: @event&.persisted? ? event_nav_items(@event) : admin_nav_items,
      back_link: @event&.persisted? ? {
        label: "Back to Events", path: admin_events_path,
        context: @event.name, context_subtitle: @event.status.humanize
      } : nil,
      footer_text: "xEvent",
      user_dropdown: user_signed_in? ? {
        email: current_user.email,
        subtitle: Current.account&.name,
        sign_out_path: destroy_user_session_path,
        avatar_bg_class: "bg-primary-subtle",
        avatar_text_class: "text-primary"
      } : nil
    } do %>
      <%= yield %>
    <% end %>
  </body>
</html>
